We are talking about from pressing power button to login prompt showing up:
    1.Firmware on the main system board selects the bootable media, and...
    2.The boot loader loads the monolithic kernel from the boot media into RAM and starts it, and...
    3.The kernel uses the directive passed by the boot loader to find the main file system, at which point it can find and run...
        Init file system
    4.The init program runs boot programs to find the other file systems and start network and local service processes.
        OpenRC, Systemd, Upstart, sysvinit